### Steps to reproduce

I'm using Mac 

using Safari browser:

1. Enable Touch ID for autofilling passwords on your Mac.
2. Run the code on the web using Safari.
3. Choose the suggested username/password from the password manager.
4. A Touch ID popup will appear. Provide your biometrics or password.

using Chrome:

1. Enable Touch ID for autofilling passwords on your Mac.
2. In Chrome open Google Password Manager -> Settings -> Make sure that "Use your screen lock when filling in passwords" is turned on and "Sign in automatically" is turned off. 
3. Re-open browser
4. Run the code on the web using Chrome
5. Save username & password for this user and localhost and try to login again using suggestions from the password manager.
6. A Touch ID popup will appear. Provide your biometrics or password.

### Expected results

When I provide either fingerprint or password for TouchId and it is correct, username(email) and password fields should be populated with data from password manager. 

### Actual results

Nothing happens. Fields seem to loose focus and are not prefilled. 

In Safari -> Fields are only prefilled when you use touchId directly, without selecting username from the list first. So without loosing focus to the field.  Otherwise you are blocked and cannot populate data using autofill. 
In Chrome -> On second try you are not asked again about TouchId, so autofill works. In that case focus is not lost from the TextFormField that is why it seems to work. 

