Cause analysis

Looks like it is because, the selection handle is put to the root Overlay, which is in navigator and thus is drawn at a higher z-index (I know flutter does not have z-index, just analogy) than the green box.

Code

<details>

```dart
import 'dart:async';

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

Future<void> main() async {
  WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatefulWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  State<MyApp> createState() => _MyAppState();
}

class _MyAppState extends State<MyApp> {
  var popup = false;

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    Timer.periodic(const Duration(seconds: 3), (timer) {
      if (!mounted) return;
      setState(() => popup = !popup);
    });
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(),
        body: Stack(
          children: [const TextField(), if (popup) Container(width: 100, height: 100, color: Colors.green)],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

</details>

Step

1. Enter some words to text field
2. Select some words in it (so selection handle appears)
3. wait until the green box appear
4. now we can see the handle still appears, though text field is occluded
5. interact with the handle, we can further see it can be interacted even though it should be occluded

